<subSubSection id="EBAF651CC23F6F2EFF308F81FBBB599A" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="A30A3697C23F6F2EFF308F81FDD6595B" blockId="14.[166,1225,1236,1423]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Remarks. This species is known from the 
<typeStatus id="7C0E8835C23F6F2EFD3C8F81FCAD58FA" box="[727,830,1236,1262]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">holotype</typeStatus>
<specimenCount id="B5B3FD1EC23F6F2EFCAD8F81FCEC58FA" box="[838,895,1236,1262]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="male">male</specimenCount>
from 
<collectingRegion id="6171F875C23F6F2EFC2C8F80FB8658FB" box="[967,1045,1237,1263]" country="China" name="Gansu" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Gansu</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="DBA27607C23F6F2EFBCA8F81FBFA58FA" box="[1057,1129,1236,1262]" name="China" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectionCode id="C5A4AE52C23F6F2EFB938F81FB2F58FB" box="[1144,1212,1236,1263]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">IZAS</collectionCode>
), unavailable in this study. According to the original description, it possesses black femora, uniformly dark brown bands on the wing, and entirely black abdominal tergites; body length Ơ = 3.7; wing length Ơ = 4.0.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A30A3697C23F6F2EFF308E01FBBB599A" blockId="14.[166,1225,1236,1423]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Additional study of the 
<typeStatus id="7C0E8835C23F6F2EFE008E00FD8E597B" box="[491,541,1365,1391]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">type</typeStatus>
and topotypic material from 
<collectingCountry id="DBA27607C23F6F2EFC858E01FC2B597A" box="[878,952,1364,1390]" name="China" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">China</collectingCountry>
, including morphology of the male and female genitalia, DNA sequences, and host plants, is needed.
</paragraph>
